  "text": "In a nutshell, the following steps are performed for all candidate peaks: (1) calculate the P value using G-test. If P value is larger than 0.05, then discard the candidate. (2) Calculate the peak score for all remaining peaks. (3) Find all sets of overlapping peaks and discard all others but the peak with the highest peak score from each set. (4) Calculate false discovery rates using the Benjamini-Hochberg procedure for dependent test statistics [CITATION_1] ) using the initial number of candidate peaks as the total number of tested null hypotheses.",
